provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html — Python abc module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/abc.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__, abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__, abc.ABCMeta._dump_registry, and abc.update_abstractmethods — Python-level methods with __code__. ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__qualname__=='ABCMeta.__instancecheck__' (len=25); ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__module__=='abc' (len=3); ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_argcount==2 (cls, instance); ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==2. ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__qualname__=='ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__' (len=25); ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_argcount==2 (cls, subclass); co_varnames.__len__()==2. ABCMeta._dump_registry.__qualname__=='ABCMeta._dump_registry' (len=22); co_argcount==2; co_varnames.__len__()==6. abc.update_abstractmethods.__qualname__=='update_abstractmethods' (len=22); co_argcount==1; co_varnames.__len__()==5. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__prepare__ and abc.ABCMeta.__subclasshook__ are builtin_function_or_method objects in Python 3.14.3 (implemented in C) and have no __code__ attribute. ABCMeta.__instancecheck__ and ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__ are Python functions (both have __code__) and share qualname length of 25. ABCMeta._dump_registry and update_abstractmethods both have qualname length of 22. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

